## Severity
Trivial
## Dimension
yagni
## Location
src/services/analytics.rs:268-287, src/services/analytics.rs:18-43
## Violation
A 20-line test (b4_cost_tracked_variant_not_yet_present_gap649) exists purely to sentinel an absent enum variant.

    /// B4 / gap #649: pin that AnalyticsEvent does NOT have a CostTracked
    /// variant yet.
    #[test]
    fn b4_cost_tracked_variant_not_yet_present_gap649() {
        let event = AnalyticsEvent::ThinkingEmitted { budget: 1 };
        let _ = match event {
            AnalyticsEvent::SessionStart { .. }
            | AnalyticsEvent::SessionEnd { .. }
            ...
            => "no CostTracked yet — see gap #649",
        };
    }

YAGNI-in-reverse: a sentinel for behaviour we DO want to add, sitting in production test code. Once #649 lands the test becomes a hidden footgun (easy to forget to delete). It also does not catch the actual gap (cost emission), only the variant's absence.
## Mandated refactor
Delete the sentinel test. Track the gap via the existing crosslink issue #649. If a compile-time check is wanted, use a const-block expecting CostTracked — the exhaustive match in TracingAnalytics::record already enforces this once the variant is added.
